{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Back in 1992, I started working for a company"},{"time":2000,"text":"called Interval Research,"},{"time":4000,"text":"which was just then being founded"},{"time":6000,"text":"by David Lidell and Paul Allen"},{"time":8000,"text":"as a for-profit research enterprise in Silicon Valley."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14000,"text":"I met with David"},{"time":16000,"text":"to talk about what I might do in his company."},{"time":19000,"text":"I was just coming out of a failed virtual reality business"},{"time":22000,"text":"and supporting myself by being on the speaking circuit"},{"time":24000,"text":"and writing books --"},{"time":26000,"text":"after twenty years or so in the computer game industry"},{"time":29000,"text":"having ideas that people didn't think they could sell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33000,"text":"And David and I discovered"},{"time":35000,"text":"that we had a question in common,"},{"time":37000,"text":"that we really wanted the answer to,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and that was,"},{"time":41000,"text":"\"Why hasn't anybody built any computer games for little girls?\""},{"time":44000,"text":"Why is that?"},{"time":46000,"text":"It can't just be a giant sexist conspiracy."},{"time":49000,"text":"These people aren't that smart."},{"time":52000,"text":"There's six billion dollars on the table."},{"time":55000,"text":"They would go for it if they could figure out how."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58000,"text":"So, what is the deal here?"},{"time":60000,"text":"And as we thought about our goals --"},{"time":63000,"text":"I should say that Interval is really a humanistic institution,"},{"time":66000,"text":"in the classical sense"},{"time":69000,"text":"that humanism, at its best,"},{"time":72000,"text":"finds a way to combine clear-eyed empirical research"},{"time":75000,"text":"with a set of core values"},{"time":78000,"text":"that fundamentally love and respect people."},{"time":81000,"text":"The basic idea of humanism"},{"time":84000,"text":"is the improvable quality of life;"},{"time":87000,"text":"that we can do good things,"},{"time":89000,"text":"that there are things worth doing"},{"time":91000,"text":"because they're good things to do,"},{"time":93000,"text":"and that clear-eyed empiricism"},{"time":95000,"text":"can help us figure out how to do them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98000,"text":"So, contrary to popular belief,"},{"time":100000,"text":"there is not a conflict of interest between empiricism and values."},{"time":105000,"text":"And Interval Research is kind of the living example"},{"time":108000,"text":"of how that can be true."},{"time":110000,"text":"So David and I decided to go find out,"},{"time":112000,"text":"through the best research we could muster,"},{"time":114000,"text":"what it would take to get a little girl"},{"time":117000,"text":"to put her hands on a computer,"},{"time":119000,"text":"to achieve the level of comfort and ease with the technology"},{"time":122000,"text":"that little boys have because they play video games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"We spent two and a half years conducting research;"},{"time":128000,"text":"we spent another year and a half in advance development."},{"time":132000,"text":"Then we formed a spin-off company."},{"time":135000,"text":"In the research phase of the project at Interval,"},{"time":139000,"text":"we partnered with a company called Cheskin Research,"},{"time":142000,"text":"and these people -- Davis Masten and Christopher Ireland --"},{"time":146000,"text":"changed my mind entirely about what market research was"},{"time":149000,"text":"and what it could be."},{"time":150000,"text":"They taught me how to look and see,"},{"time":153000,"text":"and they did not do the incredibly stupid thing"},{"time":156000,"text":"of saying to a child,"},{"time":158000,"text":"\"Of all these things we already make you,"},{"time":160000,"text":"which do you like best?\" --"},{"time":161000,"text":"which gives you zero answers that are usable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"So, what we did for the first two and a half years"},{"time":166000,"text":"was four things:"},{"time":168000,"text":"We did an extensive review of the literature"},{"time":171000,"text":"in related fields, like cognitive psychology,"},{"time":173000,"text":"spatial cognition, gender studies,"},{"time":175000,"text":"play theory, sociology, primatology."},{"time":178000,"text":"Thank you Frans de Waal, wherever you are,"},{"time":180000,"text":"I love you and I'd give anything to meet you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"After we had done that with a pretty large team of people"},{"time":186000,"text":"and discovered what we thought the salient issues were"},{"time":189000,"text":"with girls and boys and playing --"},{"time":192000,"text":"because, after all, that's really what this is about --"},{"time":195000,"text":"we moved to the second phase of our work,"},{"time":197000,"text":"where we interviewed adult experts"},{"time":200000,"text":"in academia, some of the people"},{"time":202000,"text":"who'd produced the literature that we found relevant."},{"time":204000,"text":"Also, we did focus groups with people who were on the ground with kids every day,"},{"time":207000,"text":"like playground supervisors. We talked to them,"},{"time":209000,"text":"confirmed some hypotheses and identified some serious questions"},{"time":212000,"text":"about gender difference and play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214000,"text":"Then we did what I consider to be the heart of the work:"},{"time":218000,"text":"interviewed 1,100 children, boys and girls,"},{"time":221000,"text":"ages seven to 12, all over the United States --"},{"time":224000,"text":"except for Silicon Valley, Boston and Austin"},{"time":227000,"text":"because we knew that their little families would have millions of computers in them"},{"time":231000,"text":"and they wouldn't be a representative sample."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"And at the end of those remarkable conversations"},{"time":237000,"text":"with kids and their best friends across the United States,"},{"time":240000,"text":"after two years, we pulled together some survey data from another 10,000 children,"},{"time":243000,"text":"drew up a set up of what we thought were the key findings of our research,"},{"time":252000,"text":"and spent another year transforming them into design heuristics,"},{"time":256000,"text":"for designing computer-based products --"},{"time":259000,"text":"and, in fact, any kind of products -- for little girls, ages eight to 12."},{"time":263000,"text":"And we spent that time designing interactive prototypes for computer software"},{"time":268000,"text":"and testing them with little girls."},{"time":270000,"text":"In 1996, in November, we formed the company Purple Moon"},{"time":275000,"text":"which was a spinoff of Interval Research,"},{"time":277000,"text":"and our chief investors were Interval Research, Vulcan Northwest,"},{"time":280000,"text":"Institutional Venture Partners and Allen and Company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"We launched a website on September 2nd"},{"time":287000,"text":"that has now served 25 million pages,"},{"time":289000,"text":"and has 42,000 registered young girl users."},{"time":294000,"text":"They visit an average of one and a half times a day,"},{"time":298000,"text":"spend an average of 35 minutes a visit,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and look at 50 pages a visit."},{"time":303000,"text":"So we feel that we've formed a successful online community with girls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308000,"text":"We launched two titles in October --"},{"time":310000,"text":"\"Rockett's New School\" -- the first of a series"},{"time":312000,"text":"of products -- is about a character called Rockett beginning her first day of school"},{"time":316000,"text":"in eighth grade at a brand new place, with a blank slate,"},{"time":319000,"text":"which allows girls to play with the question of, \"What will I be like when I'm older?\""},{"time":325000,"text":"\"What's it going to be like to be in high school or junior high school?"},{"time":328000,"text":"Who are my friends?\";"},{"time":330000,"text":"to exercise the love of social complexity"},{"time":332000,"text":"and the narrative intelligence that drives most of their play behavior;"},{"time":336000,"text":"and which embeds in it values about noticing that we have lots of choices"},{"time":342000,"text":"in our lives and the ways that we conduct ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"The other title that we launched is called \"Secret Paths in the Forest,\""},{"time":348000,"text":"which addresses the more fantasy-oriented, inner lives of girls."},{"time":351000,"text":"These two titles both showed up in the top 50 entertainment titles in PC Data --"},{"time":356000,"text":"entertainment titles in PC Data"},{"time":359000,"text":"in December, right up there with \"John Madden Football,\""},{"time":363000,"text":"which thrills me to death."},{"time":365000,"text":"So, we're real,"},{"time":367000,"text":"and we've touched several hundreds of thousands of little girls."},{"time":371000,"text":"We've made half-a-billion impressions"},{"time":374000,"text":"with marketing and PR for this brand, Purple Moon."},{"time":378000,"text":"Ninety-six percent of them, roughly, have been positive;"},{"time":381000,"text":"four percent of them have been \"other.\""},{"time":383000,"text":"I want to talk about the other,"},{"time":385000,"text":"because the politics of this enterprise, in a way,"},{"time":388000,"text":"have been the most fascinating part of it, for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"There are really two kinds of negative reviews that we've received."},{"time":394000,"text":"One kind of reviewer is a male gamer"},{"time":398000,"text":"who thinks he knows what games ought to be,"},{"time":400000,"text":"and won't show the product to little girls."},{"time":403000,"text":"The other kind of reviewer is a certain flavor of feminist"},{"time":407000,"text":"who thinks they know what little girls ought to be."},{"time":410000,"text":"And so it's funny to me that these interesting, odd bedfellows"},{"time":416000,"text":"have one thing in common:"},{"time":418000,"text":"they don't listen to little girls."},{"time":422000,"text":"They haven't looked at children"},{"time":425000,"text":"and they're certainly not demonstrating any love for them."},{"time":429000,"text":"I'd like to play you some voices of little girls"},{"time":432000,"text":"from the two-and-a-half years of research that we did --"},{"time":434000,"text":"actually, some of the voices are more recent."},{"time":436000,"text":"And these voices will be accompanied by photographs"},{"time":439000,"text":"that they took for us of their lives,"},{"time":441000,"text":"of the things that they value and care about."},{"time":443000,"text":"These are pictures the girls themselves never saw, but they gave to us"},{"time":446000,"text":"This is the stuff those reviewers don't know about and aren't listening to"},{"time":451000,"text":"and this is the kind of research I recommend to those"},{"time":453000,"text":"who want to do humanistic work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"Girl 1: Yeah, my character is usually a tomboy."},{"time":457000,"text":"Hers is more into boys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"Girl 2: Uh, yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461000,"text":"Girl 1: We have -- in the very beginning of the whole game, always we do this:"},{"time":464000,"text":"we each have a piece of paper; we write down our name, our age --"},{"time":467000,"text":"are we rich, very rich, not rich, poor, medium, wealthy,"},{"time":473000,"text":"boyfriends, dogs, pets -- what else -- sisters, brothers, and all those."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480000,"text":"Girl 2: Divorced -- parents divorced, maybe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"Girl 3: This is my pretend [unclear] one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"Girl 4: We make a school newspaper on the computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"Girl 5: For a girl's game also usually they'll have really pretty scenery"},{"time":494000,"text":"with clouds and flowers."},{"time":496000,"text":"Girl 6: Like, if you were a girl and you were really adventurous and a real big tomboy,"},{"time":500000,"text":"you would think that girls' games were kinda sissy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504000,"text":"Girl 7: I run track, I played soccer,"},{"time":508000,"text":"I play basketball, and I love a lot of things to do."},{"time":511000,"text":"And sometimes I feel like I can't really enjoy myself unless it's like a vacation,"},{"time":519000,"text":"like when I get Mondays and all those days off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"Girl 8: Well, sometimes there is a lot of stuff going on"},{"time":526000,"text":"because I have music lessons and I'm on swim team --"},{"time":530000,"text":"all this different stuff that I have to do,"},{"time":533000,"text":"and sometimes it gets overwhelming."},{"time":536000,"text":"Girl 9: My friend Justine"},{"time":540000,"text":"kinda took my friend Kelly, and now they're being mean to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544000,"text":"Girl 10: Well, sometimes it gets annoying when your brothers and sisters,"},{"time":547000,"text":"or brother or sister, when they copy you and you get your idea first"},{"time":552000,"text":"and they take your idea and they do it themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"Girl 11: Because my older sister, she gets everything"},{"time":561000,"text":"and, like, when I ask my mom for something, she'll say, \"No\" -- all the time."},{"time":565000,"text":"But she gives my sister everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"Brenda Laurel: I want to show you, real quickly, just a minute"},{"time":569000,"text":"of \"Rockett's Tricky Decision,\" which went gold two days ago."},{"time":572000,"text":"Let's hope it's really stable."},{"time":575000,"text":"This is the second day in Rockett's life."},{"time":578000,"text":"The reason I'm showing you this"},{"time":580000,"text":"is I'm hoping that the scene that I'm going to show you will look familiar"},{"time":584000,"text":"and sound familiar, now that you've listened to some girls' voices."},{"time":587000,"text":"And you can see how we've tried to incorporate the issues that matter to them"},{"time":592000,"text":"in the game that we've created."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597000,"text":"Miko: Hey Rockett! C'mere!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":599000,"text":"Rockett: Hi Miko! What's going on?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601000,"text":"Miko: Did you hear about Nakilia's big Halloween party this weekend?"},{"time":604000,"text":"She asked me to make sure you knew about it."},{"time":606000,"text":"Nakilia invited Reuben too, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":609000,"text":"Rockett: But what? Isn't he coming?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"Miko: I don't think so."},{"time":613000,"text":"I mean, I heard his band is playing at another party the same night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616000,"text":"Rockett: Really? What other party?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":620000,"text":"Girl: Max's party is going to be so cool, Whitney."},{"time":624000,"text":"He's invited all the best people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626000,"text":"BL: I'm going to fast-forward to the decision point"},{"time":629000,"text":"because I know I don't have a lot of time."},{"time":631000,"text":"After this awful event occurs, Rocket gets to decide how she feels about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"Rockett: Who'd want to show up at that party anyway?"},{"time":638000,"text":"I could get invited to that party any day if I wanted to."},{"time":642000,"text":"Gee, I doubt I'll make Max's best people list."}]},{"cues":[{"time":646000,"text":"BL: OK, so we're going to emotionally navigate."},{"time":648000,"text":"If we were playing the game, that's what we'd do."},{"time":650000,"text":"If at any time during the game we want to learn more about the characters,"},{"time":653000,"text":"we can go into this hidden hallway,"},{"time":655000,"text":"and I'll quickly just show you the interface."},{"time":658000,"text":"We can, for example, go find Miko's locker"},{"time":663000,"text":"and get some more information about her."},{"time":666000,"text":"Oops, I turned the wrong way."},{"time":668000,"text":"But you get the general idea of the product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"I wanted to show you the ways, innocuous as they seem,"},{"time":673000,"text":"in which we're incorporating what we've learned about girls --"},{"time":676000,"text":"their desires to experience greater emotional flexibility,"},{"time":680000,"text":"and to play around with the social complexity of their lives."},{"time":686000,"text":"I want to make the point that what we're giving girls, I think, through this effort,"},{"time":692000,"text":"is a kind of validation,"},{"time":695000,"text":"a sense of being seen."},{"time":697000,"text":"And a sense of the choices that are available in their lives."},{"time":700000,"text":"We love them."},{"time":702000,"text":"We see them."},{"time":704000,"text":"We're not trying to tell them who they ought to be."},{"time":706000,"text":"But we're really, really happy about who they are."},{"time":709000,"text":"It turns out they're really great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"I want to close by showing you a videotape"},{"time":715000,"text":"that's a version of a future game in the Rockett series"},{"time":719000,"text":"that our graphic artists and design people put together,"},{"time":723000,"text":"that we feel would please that four percent of reviewers."},{"time":758000,"text":"\"Rockett 28!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":765000,"text":"Rockett: It's like I'm just waking up, you know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"BL: Thanks."}]}]}